attVpnGatewayMIB.name: attVpnGatewayMIB

revisions.description: Added reporting of data usage statistics, support a ping list, return the circuit speed, tunnel enhancements. Supported by AT&T VPN Gateways running at least version 6.2.

Changes to reflect device name change from AT&T NetGate to AT&T VPN Gateway. 'attVpnGateway' is the preferred subtree name instead of 'attNetGate'. Added evVrrpStateChange trap for VRRP state changes. Added several new items to the ng3GInfo section. The naming convention in this section now has items starting with 'cell' instead of 'ng3g'. Existing OIDs will not be renamed to maintain compatibility. Adding reporting of tunnel automation to the ngTunnelInfo section. The naming convention in this section now has items starting with 'tun' instead of 'ngtu'. Existing OIDs will not be renamed to maintain compatibility. Adding reporting of time in backup to the interface section. The naming convention in this section now has items starting with 'if' instead of 'ngif'. Existing OIDs will not be renamed to maintain compatibility. Supported by AT&T VPN Gateways running at least version 6.1.

Changed nghwWanConnectionMethod and nghwCurrentWanConnectionMethod so that wanAnalogDial is used instead of wanConfigDialPri. Also wanConfigCellularDial is now used instead of wanConfigCellularPri. Supported by AT&T VPN Gateways running at least version 6.0.

Added the ngevCellModemRequired trap to alert when the cell modem is not found or removed. Added cell modem status to the ng3GInfo section. Remove the range from the syntax for ng3gSlotNum because a -1 is returned when no card is found. Added support for IPv6 for polling and traps/informs. Added active WAN interface to excessive dial trap. Supported by AT&T VPN Gateways running at least version 5.3.

Changed timestamps in polling fields to use the standard DateAndTime format. Previously only fields in traps could be in DateAndTime format. Added nghwPorts section for more detailed info about hardware ports. Added ngev8200VPortDown trap. Supported by AT&T VPN Gateways running at least version 5.0.
Added free-format customer field. Supported by AT&T VPN Gateways running at least version 4.10.

Added traps for secondary authentication and switch user attempts. These traps are supported by AT&T VPN Gateways running at least version 4.9. Added max threshold to excessive dial trap. Changes made for strict MIB compliance. More OIDs added to ng3GInfo section. Added a new section called ngDialInfo that contains some of the dial configuration information (regardless of whether a cellular card is in use or not). Supported by AT&T VPN Gateways running at least version 4.9.

Added traps that the AT&T VPN Gateways can send. Added firewall sections that report on the firewall tables, chains, and rules active on the device. Added total time the dial connection has been active. Added current number and max number of ip_conntrack entries. Supported by AT&T VPN Gateways running at least version 4.8.

attVpnGatewayMIB.contactinfo: Please contact your AT&T Account Representative.
attVpnGatewayMIB.description: The MIB module for the AT&T VPN Gateway.

nghwAccount.name: nghwAccount
nghwAccount.description: The account in Service Manager this device is registered under.

nghwUtcOffset.name: nghwUtcOffset
nghwUtcOffset.description: Indicates how many minutes away from UTC time the device is located. Values must be in 30 minute increments. Valid range is -840 to 840.

nghwDstAllowed.name: nghwDstAllowed
nghwDstAllowed.description: Indicates if the device is located in an area that observes daylight savings time.

nghwDstActive.name: nghwDstActive
nghwDstActive.description: Indicates if daylight savings time is current active at this date and time.

nghwWanConnectionMethod.name: nghwWanConnectionMethod
nghwWanConnectionMethod.description: The current primary IPv4 WAN connection setting. This is configured via the web interface and is not read from Service Manager.

nghwHostname.name: nghwHostname
nghwHostname.description: The name of the current host.

ngDnsTable.name: ngDnsTable
ngDnsTable.description: The (conceptual) table of DNS on the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage table for each DNS.

ngDnsEntry.name: ngDnsEntry
ngDnsEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical DNS area on the host.

ngdnIndex.name: ngdnIndex
ngdnIndex.description: A unique value for each logical DNS contained on the device.

ngdnServer.name: ngdnServer
ngdnServer.description: The IP address of an indivdual name server in use.

ngDnsIPv6Table.name: ngDnsIPv6Table
ngDnsIPv6Table.description: The (conceptual) table of IPv6 DNS on the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage table for each DNS.

ngDnsIPv6Entry.name: ngDnsIPv6Entry
ngDnsIPv6Entry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical IPv6 DNS area on the host.

ngdnIPv6Index.name: ngdnIPv6Index
ngdnIPv6Index.description: A unique value for each logical IPv6 DNS contained on the device.

ngdnIPv6Server.name: ngdnIPv6Server
ngdnIPv6Server.description: The IPv6 IP address of an indivdual name server in use.

nghwLanguage.name: nghwLanguage
nghwLanguage.description: The language that will be displayed on the CGI web interface. The valid values are: EN = English JA = Japanese ES = Spanish BP = Brazil Portuguese FC = French Canadian TC = Traditional Chinese SC = Simplified Chinese

ngCustCommTable.name: ngCustCommTable
ngCustCommTable.description: The (conceptual) table of customer info (such as comments) on the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage table for each one.

ngCustCommEntry.name: ngCustCommEntry
ngCustCommEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical customer comment area on the host.

ngcuIndex.name: ngcuIndex
ngcuIndex.description: A unique value for each logical customer info.

ngcuCustComment.name: ngcuCustComment
ngcuCustComment.description: A free-format field that can be added to the AT&T VPN Gateway's profile at a customer's request. Currently only one comment field can be specified.

ngPortTable.name: ngPortTable
ngPortTable.description: The (conceptual) table of ports on the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage table for each port.

ngPortEntry.name: ngPortEntry
ngPortEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical port area on the host.

ngpoIndex.name: ngpoIndex
ngpoIndex.description: A unique value for each logical port contained on the device.

ngpoStatus.name: ngpoStatus
ngpoStatus.description: The link status of an individual hardware port.

nghwCurrentWanConnectionMethod.name: nghwCurrentWanConnectionMethod
nghwCurrentWanConnectionMethod.description: The currently active IPv4 WAN connection, which may differ from the configured primary IPv4 WAN connection setting. For example, the primary IPv4 WAN is configured for DHCP (wanConfigDHCP), but because of a network outage the PPPoE secondary WAN connection (wanConfigPPPoE2) is currently providing connectivity.

nghwIPv6WanConnectionMethod.name: nghwIPv6WanConnectionMethod
nghwIPv6WanConnectionMethod.description: The current primary IPv6 WAN connection setting. This is configured via the web interface and is not read from Service Manager.

nghwIPv6CurrentWanConnectionMethod.name: nghwIPv6CurrentWanConnectionMethod
nghwIPv6CurrentWanConnectionMethod.description: The currently active IPv6 WAN connection, which may differ from the configured primary IPv6 WAN connection setting. For example, the primary IPv4 WAN is configured for DHCP (wanConfigIPv6DHCP), but because of a network outage the static IP secondary WAN connection (wanConfigIPv6Static2) is currently providing connectivity.

nghwLastFullQueryTimeDAT.name: nghwLastFullQueryTimeDAT
nghwLastFullQueryTimeDAT.description: The last time when the AT&T VPN Gateway was successfully able to retrieve its full profile from an AT&T Administration Server.

nghwLastAnyQueryTimeDAT.name: nghwLastAnyQueryTimeDAT
nghwLastAnyQueryTimeDAT.description: The last time when the AT&T VPN Gateway was successfully able to retrieve its profile from an AT&T Administration Server. If this time does not match nghwLastFullQueryTimeDAT then that means only part of the profile was retrieved. This is to prevent any possible reboots if critical portions of the profile were to change.

nghwLastUpgradeTimeDAT.name: nghwLastUpgradeTimeDAT
nghwLastUpgradeTimeDAT.description: The last time when the software version of AT&T VPN Gateway was successfully upgraded. Returns January 1 year 0 time 0 when this cannot be determined.

hwMac.name: hwMac
hwMac.description: The main WAN MAC address of this device used to identify its profile in Service Manager.

hwRollbackVersion.name: hwRollbackVersion
hwRollbackVersion.description: Software code version that will be used if the rollback feature is activated.

hwDualWan.name: hwDualWan
hwDualWan.description: Ties to the 'Use as Internet Primary' field in Service Manager. Controls the Dual WAN configuration.

hwWan2ConnectionMethod.name: hwWan2ConnectionMethod
hwWan2ConnectionMethod.description: The current WAN2 IPv4 WAN connection setting. This is not configured via the web interface and is read from Service Manager.

hwIPv6Wan2ConnectionMethod.name: hwIPv6Wan2ConnectionMethod
hwIPv6Wan2ConnectionMethod.description: The current WAN2 IPv6 WAN connection setting. This is not configured via the web interface and is read from Service Manager.

hwWan1GwayMac.name: hwWan1GwayMac
hwWan1GwayMac.description: This is the MAC Address of the WAN1 Gateway router if it is in use. For MAC Address range from 002704000000 to 002704009999, it is a NetBridge (SX) device. For MAC Address range from 002704010000 to 002704010425, it is a NetBridge (FX) device. For MAC Address range from 002704010426 to 002704019999, it is a Cell Extender (6200-FX) device. For MAC Address range from 002704270000 to 002704279999, it is a Cell Extender (6300-CX) device.

hwWan2Mac.name: hwWan2Mac
hwWan2Mac.description: This is the MAC Address of the WAN2 interface if it is in use.

hwWan2GwayMac.name: hwWan2GwayMac
hwWan2GwayMac.description: This is the MAC Address of the WAN2 Gateway router if it is in use. For MAC Address range from 002704000000 to 002704009999, it is a NetBridge (SX) device. For MAC Address range from 002704010000 to 002704010425, it is a NetBridge (FX) device. For MAC Address range from 002704010426 to 002704019999, it is a Cell Extender (6200-FX) device. For MAC Address range from 002704270000 to 002704279999, it is a Cell Extender (6300-CX) device.

ngifActiveWanIface.name: ngifActiveWanIface
ngifActiveWanIface.description: The interface that is currently in use for the primary connection.

ngifTotalBytesIn.name: ngifTotalBytesIn
ngifTotalBytesIn.description: Total bytes in on the active WAN interface.

ngifTotalBytesOut.name: ngifTotalBytesOut
ngifTotalBytesOut.description: Total bytes out on the active WAN interface.

ngifTimeInDial.name: ngifTimeInDial
ngifTimeInDial.description: How long the current dial connection has been up.

ifTimeInBackup.name: ifTimeInBackup
ifTimeInBackup.description: How long the backup connection has been up. This is very similar to ngifTimeInDial. The difference is that ngifTimeInDial isn't necessarily measuring a backup connection. For example, when configured for 'Dial As Primary' ifTimeInBackup will always remain zero because there is no backup for Dial As Primary but ngifTimeInDial will be non-zero when the connection is up. In other WAN configurations (such as DHCP, for example) both ngifTimeInDial and ifTimeInBackup will be non-zero when the backup connection is in use.

ifInterfaceFormat.name: ifInterfaceFormat
ifInterfaceFormat.description: Setting from the Service Manager profile that controls SNMP interface persistence. Zero indicates that this feature is not in use.

ifStatTable.name: ifStatTable
ifStatTable.description: The (conceptual) table of interface statistics on the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage table for each interface statistic.

ifStatEntry.name: ifStatEntry
ifStatEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical interface statistic area.

ifStatsMainIndex.name: ifStatsMainIndex
ifStatsMainIndex.description: A unique value for each logical interface statistic.

ifStatsifIndex.name: ifStatsifIndex
ifStatsifIndex.description: The value of this index reported by ifIndex in the standard MIBs. This is needed because index numbers can be skipped in the standard MIBs.

ifStatsifDescr.name: ifStatsifDescr
ifStatsifDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the interface.

ifStatsRxCrcErr.name: ifStatsRxCrcErr
ifStatsRxCrcErr.description: Received CRC errors for the interface.

ifCircuitSpeed.name: ifCircuitSpeed
ifCircuitSpeed.description: Informational string that is pulled from the device profile. Useful for the scenario where the physical connection to the WAN interface will be 10, 100 or 1000 Mbps (depending on the ISP modem/router) but the speed allocated by the ISP will be much lower (2, 4, or 8 Mbps). This field does not control speed and does not indicate a measurement of speed. It is manually entered by an administrator for informational purposes only.

ngVlanTable.name: ngVlanTable
ngVlanTable.description: The (conceptual) table of VLANs on the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage table for each VLAN.

ngVlanEntry.name: ngVlanEntry
ngVlanEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical VLAN area on the host.

ngvlIndex.name: ngvlIndex
ngvlIndex.description: A unique value for each logical VLAN contained by the device.

ngvlId.name: ngvlId
ngvlId.description: This is the number assigned to the VLAN. Please note: A VLAN with an ID of 4070 is a special VLAN used to hold ports that are disabled.

ngvlPorts.name: ngvlPorts
ngvlPorts.description: The ports assigned to the VLAN.

ngvlSpeed.name: ngvlSpeed
ngvlSpeed.description: This is the speed supported on the VLAN Ethernet interfaces. If the VLAN Ethernet speed is configured for auto negotiation then autoNegot will be reported and the negotiated speed will be reported by ngvlSpeedCurrent. If the VLAN Ethernet speed is configured for a specific speed that speed will be reported.

ngvlIpRange.name: ngvlIpRange
ngvlIpRange.description: The range of IP addresses handed out via DHCP on this VLAN. Values will be 0.0.0.0 0.0.0.0 if DHCP is not enabled on this VLAN. Followed by number of addresses assigned and number of total addresses. NOTE: As of AT&T VPN Gateway version 5.3 the number of addresses assigned will no longer be returned. A zero will be returned for that field.

ngvlDhcpRelayAddr.name: ngvlDhcpRelayAddr
ngvlDhcpRelayAddr.description: When the DHCP Type is 'R', this is the address the AT&T VPN Gateway devices uses to relay DHCP requests. This field is required when the DHCP Type is 'R'. A second address can be specified.

ngvlDhcpDefRoute.name: ngvlDhcpDefRoute
ngvlDhcpDefRoute.description: This field is required when VRRP Active Indicator is 'Y' and is optional otherwise. If specified, it must be within the local LAN subnet of the AT&T VPN Gateway but cannot fall within the DHCP pool start and end addresses. For the DHCP Default Route on the AT&T VPN Gateway device profile, if entered, the address must be within the network specified by the LAN Address and LAN Subnet, but not within the address range specified by the DHCP Start Address and DHCP End Address.

ngvlLanAddr.name: ngvlLanAddr
ngvlLanAddr.description: This is the LAN address for the device on the VLAN.

ngvlLanSubAddr.name: ngvlLanSubAddr
ngvlLanSubAddr.description: This is the LAN subnet address for the device on the VLAN.

ngvlIPv6IpRangeStart.name: ngvlIPv6IpRangeStart
ngvlIPv6IpRangeStart.description: The start of the range of IPv6 IP addresses handed out via DHCP on this VLAN. Value will be all zeroes if DHCP is not enabled on this VLAN.

ngvlIPv6IpRangeEnd.name: ngvlIPv6IpRangeEnd
ngvlIPv6IpRangeEnd.description: The end of the range of IPv6 IP addresses handed out via DHCP on this VLAN. Value will be all zeroes if DHCP is not enabled on this VLAN.

ngvlIPv6DhcpRelayAddrPri.name: ngvlIPv6DhcpRelayAddrPri
ngvlIPv6DhcpRelayAddrPri.description: When the DHCP Type is 'R', this is the primary address the AT&T VPN Gateway devices uses to relay DHCP requests. This field is required when the DHCP Type is 'R' and IPv6 is in use.

ngvlIPv6DhcpRelayAddrBak.name: ngvlIPv6DhcpRelayAddrBak
ngvlIPv6DhcpRelayAddrBak.description: When the DHCP Type is 'R', this is the primary address the AT&T VPN Gateway devices uses to relay DHCP requests.

ngvlIPv6LanAddr.name: ngvlIPv6LanAddr
ngvlIPv6LanAddr.description: This is the IPv6 LAN address for the device on the VLAN.

ngvlIPv6LanPrefix.name: ngvlIPv6LanPrefix
ngvlIPv6LanPrefix.description: This is the IPv6 LAN prefix for the device on the VLAN.

ngvlSpeedCurrent.name: ngvlSpeedCurrent
ngvlSpeedCurrent.description: This is the current speed in use on the VLAN Ethernet interfaces. This is helpful to determine what was chosen if the speed was set to auto negotiate. If the VLAN Ethernet speed is configured for auto negotiation then the negotiated speed will be reported. If the VLAN Ethernet speed is configured for auto negotiation and there is no link then noLink will be reported. If the VLAN Ethernet speed is configured for a specific speed that speed will be reported.

ngVrrpTable.name: ngVrrpTable
ngVrrpTable.description: The (conceptual) table of VRRPs on the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage table for each VRRP.

ngVrrpEntry.name: ngVrrpEntry
ngVrrpEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical VRRP area on the host.

ngvrIndex.name: ngvrIndex
ngvrIndex.description: A unique value for each logical VRRP contained by the device.

ngvrIface.name: ngvrIface
ngvrIface.description: The interface associated with this VRRP.

ngvrMasterStatus.name: ngvrMasterStatus
ngvrMasterStatus.description: Shows what the status is (master, backup, not active).

ngvrPriority.name: ngvrPriority
ngvrPriority.description: VRRP_PRIO_OWNER 255 /* priority of the ip owner -- rfc2338.5.3.4 */ VRRP_PRIO_DFL 100 /* default priority -- rfc2338.5.3.4 */ VRRP_PRIO_STOP 0 /* priority to stop -- rfc2338.5.3.4 */

ng3GTable.name: ng3GTable
ng3GTable.description: The (conceptual) table of 3G cards on the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage table for each 3G card.

ng3GEntry.name: ng3GEntry
ng3GEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical 3G card area on the host.

ng3gIndex.name: ng3gIndex
ng3gIndex.description: A unique value for each logical 3G card contained by the device.

ng3gSlotNum.name: ng3gSlotNum
ng3gSlotNum.description: The slot the card is plugged into. Returns -1 if no card is found. NOTE: this refers to PCMCIA slots, not USB ports.

ng3gID.name: ng3gID
ng3gID.description: Either the IMEI or ESN depending on the card.

ng3gSignalStrength.name: ng3gSignalStrength
ng3gSignalStrength.description: Signal Strength at the connect. This value will remain zero if cellBars is non-zero.

ng3gApnUser.name: ng3gApnUser
ng3gApnUser.description: The APN userid. Only populated when the access point name exists.

ng3gApnPassword.name: ng3gApnPassword
ng3gApnPassword.description: The APN password. Only populated when the access point name exists.

ng3gCellModemPresent.name: ng3gCellModemPresent
ng3gCellModemPresent.description: If the cellular modem is a supported unit that allows the AT&T VPN Gateway to query its current status then this value will indicate whether or not the unit is physically present. Unsupported units will always have a value of 'unknown'.

ng3gSIMCardNumber.name: ng3gSIMCardNumber
ng3gSIMCardNumber.description: The SIM number of the card.

ng3gDeviceType.name: ng3gDeviceType
ng3gDeviceType.description: The type of hardware of the cellular modem.

cellCollectionTimeDAT.name: cellCollectionTimeDAT
cellCollectionTimeDAT.description: The date and time the cell stats were collected. Not set if the date and time on the device hasn't been set yet.

cellConnStatus.name: cellConnStatus
cellConnStatus.description: The current status of the cellular connection.

cellMCC.name: cellMCC
cellMCC.description: A mobile country code (MCC) is used in combination with a mobile network code (MNC) (also known as a MCC / MNC tuple) to uniquely identify a mobile phone operator (carrier) using the GSM, UMTS, LTE, and iDEN public land mobile networks as well as some CDMA, TETRA, and satellite mobile networks.

cellCID.name: cellCID
cellCID.description: A GSM Cell ID (CID) is a generally unique number used to identify each Base transceiver station (BTS) or sector of a BTS within a Location area code (LAC) if not within a GSM network. In some cases the last digit of CID represents cells' Sector ID. A valid CID ranges from 0 to 65535 on GSM and CDMA networks and from 0 to 268435455 on UMTS and LTE networks.

cellBars.name: cellBars
cellBars.description: A number indicating the signal strength as a bar count. If this value is non-zero then ng3gSignalStrength will return zero.

cellRSRP.name: cellRSRP
cellRSRP.description: References LTE signals: Reference Signal Received Power is the average power of resource elements that carry cellular specific reference signals over the entire bandwidth. Valid values : all values are valid. Typical values are between -199 and -85. The larger the number (-85 for instance) the better the signal.

cellRSRQ.name: cellRSRQ
cellRSRQ.description: References LTE Signals: represents the Cell Quality.

cellSINR.name: cellSINR
cellSINR.description: References LTE signals: LTE - The signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio of the modem.

cellSNR.name: cellSNR
cellSNR.description: References LTE signals: The signal-to-noise ratio of the modem.

cellIface.name: cellIface
cellIface.description: The interface on the device associated with this cell modem.

ngTunnelTable.name: ngTunnelTable
ngTunnelTable.description: The (conceptual) table of tunnels on the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage table for each tunnel.

ngTunnelEntry.name: ngTunnelEntry
ngTunnelEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical tunnel area on the host.

ngtuIndex.name: ngtuIndex
ngtuIndex.description: A unique value for each logical tunnel contained by the device.

ngtuIpsecIface.name: ngtuIpsecIface
ngtuIpsecIface.description: The ipsec interface associated with the tunnel.

ngtuAuthState.name: ngtuAuthState
ngtuAuthState.description: An internal state used to indicate the tunnel's current operation.

ngtuState.name: ngtuState
ngtuState.description: An internal state used to indicate the tunnel's status. This state was created because the ngtuAuthState can change while the tunnel is still up. For example, when the clock is being set. This state is always attTunnelUp when the tunnel is up.

ngtuDuration.name: ngtuDuration
ngtuDuration.description: How long the tunnel has been up.

ngtuEndpoint.name: ngtuEndpoint
ngtuEndpoint.description: IP of the endpoint the tunnel is connected to. Populated if the ngtuState is 'up'.

ngtuEndpointType.name: ngtuEndpointType
ngtuEndpointType.description: Type of the endpoint the tunnel is connected to. Populated if the ngtuState is 'up'.

ngtuAuthType.name: ngtuAuthType
ngtuAuthType.description: Indicates the authentication server that will be used by the tunnel endpoint.

ngtuReasonCode.name: ngtuReasonCode
ngtuReasonCode.description: A numeric value that indicates why an inbound or outbound tunnel came down. The one exception is tnlAlive, which is sent for the tunnel 'alive' message for a tunnel that is still up.

ngtuIPv6Endpoint.name: ngtuIPv6Endpoint
ngtuIPv6Endpoint.description: IPv6 IP of the endpoint the tunnel is connected to. Populated if the ngtuState is 'up' and IPv6 is in use.

tunCurrAutomation.name: tunCurrAutomation
tunCurrAutomation.description: The tunnel automation that is currently in use and whether or not it is currently active. NOTE: Active does not necessarily mean that the tunnel is up. It could mean that the tunnel is up, in the process of coming up, or is in a state where it will be brought up if the right conditions are met. There is no automation for User Initiated mode.

tunInitVpnCon.name: tunInitVpnCon
tunInitVpnCon.description: The tunnel automation (if any) configured for the primary connection in Service Manager. If configured for User Initiated the user can choose to override that setting from the CGI interface and select Persistent or Traffic Initiated instead.

tunInitVpnBkupCon.name: tunInitVpnBkupCon
tunInitVpnBkupCon.description: Similar to tunInitVpnCon except that this controls tunnel automation via the backup connection.

tunConnectionId.name: tunConnectionId
tunConnectionId.description: The tunnel connection ID is a unique value assigned to each instance of a tunnel. It is used to associate the tunnel up, tunnel alive, and tunnel down traps together. When a tunnel goes down and is then re-established it will be assigned a new tunnel connection ID. This is the same value reported by ngevTunConnectionId in traps.

tunName.name: tunName
tunName.description: The name associated with this tunnel. Note that the name will be 'settings' if multi-tunnel is disabled.

tunDirection.name: tunDirection
tunDirection.description: Indicates whether this is an inbound or outbound tunnel.

ngcoEnabled.name: ngcoEnabled
ngcoEnabled.description: Indicates if COS is enabled or not. As of version 6.2 bandwidth testing can be active without COS being enabled. When that happens ngcoEnabled will return zero (notActive) but ngcoNextTestTimeDAT will not return January 1 year 0 time 0 for the time.

ngcoNextTestTime.name: ngcoNextTestTime
ngcoNextTestTime.description: When the next bandwidth test is scheduled to run. MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM:SS. Returns '00/00/0000 00:00:00' when no test is scheduled. The time returned is the local time on the AT&T VPN Gateway. To determine how the AT&T VPN Gateway's local time relates to UTC view the following OIDs: nghwUtcOffset (current UTC offset), nghwDstAllowed (daylight saving time allowed), nghwDstActive (daylight savings time active). NOTE: This entry is made obsolete by ngcoNextTestTimeDAT.

ngcoCurUpstreamBandw.name: ngcoCurUpstreamBandw
ngcoCurUpstreamBandw.description: Current upstream bandwidth high water mark in use.

ngcoCurDownstreamBandw.name: ngcoCurDownstreamBandw
ngcoCurDownstreamBandw.description: Current downstream bandwidth high water mark in use.

ngcoNextTestTimeDAT.name: ngcoNextTestTimeDAT
ngcoNextTestTimeDAT.description: When the next bandwidth test is scheduled to run. Returns January 1 year 0 time 0 when no test is scheduled. NOTE: This entry replaces ngcoNextTestTime.

ngcoLastTestTimeDAT.name: ngcoLastTestTimeDAT
ngcoLastTestTimeDAT.description: The date and time of when the last bandwidth test was performed. NOTE: The date and time of high water marks retained after a reboot will return January 1 year 0 time 0 for the time.

ngcoLastUpstreamResult.name: ngcoLastUpstreamResult
ngcoLastUpstreamResult.description: The upstream bandwidth measured when the last bandwidth test was performed.

ngcoLastDownstreamResult.name: ngcoLastDownstreamResult
ngcoLastDownstreamResult.description: The downstream bandwidth measured when the last bandwidth test was performed.

ngBasicComplianceRev.name: ngBasicComplianceRev
ngBasicComplianceRev.description: The compliance statement for AT&T VPN Gateway entities which implement this MIB module.

ngFirewallTable.name: ngFirewallTable
ngFirewallTable.description: The (conceptual) table of firewall tables on the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage table for each table.

ngFirewallTableEntry.name: ngFirewallTableEntry
ngFirewallTableEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical firewall table area on the host.

ngfwTableIndex.name: ngfwTableIndex
ngfwTableIndex.description: A unique value for each logical firewall table contained by the device.

ngfwTableNumberOfChains.name: ngfwTableNumberOfChains
ngfwTableNumberOfChains.description: The number of chains in this particular table.

ngFirewallChainTable.name: ngFirewallChainTable
ngFirewallChainTable.description: The (conceptual) chain of firewall chains on the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage chain for each chain.

ngFirewallChainEntry.name: ngFirewallChainEntry
ngFirewallChainEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical firewall chain area on the host.

ngfwChainIndex.name: ngfwChainIndex
ngfwChainIndex.description: A unique value for each logical firewall chain contained by the device.

ngfwChainTableIndex.name: ngfwChainTableIndex
ngfwChainTableIndex.description: Shows what table this chain belongs to. Corresponds to ngfwTableIndex in ngFirewallTable.

ngfwChainsNumberOfRules.name: ngfwChainsNumberOfRules
ngfwChainsNumberOfRules.description: The number of rules in this particular chain.

ngFirewallRuleTable.name: ngFirewallRuleTable
ngFirewallRuleTable.description: The (conceptual) table of firewall rules on the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage rule for each rule.

ngFirewallRuleEntry.name: ngFirewallRuleEntry
ngFirewallRuleEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical firewall rule area on the host.

ngfwRuleIndex.name: ngfwRuleIndex

ngfwIpConntrackMaxNumEntries.description: The maximum number of entries in the ip_conntrack file.

ngIPv6FirewallTableEntry.name: ngIPv6FirewallTableEntry
ngIPv6FirewallTableEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical IPv6 firewall table area on the host.

ngfwIPv6TableIndex.name: ngfwIPv6TableIndex
ngfwIPv6TableIndex.description: A unique value for each logical IPv6 firewall table contained by the device.

ngfwIPv6TableNumberOfChains.name: ngfwIPv6TableNumberOfChains
ngfwIPv6TableNumberOfChains.description: The number of chains in this particular table.

ngIPv6FirewallChainTable.description: The (conceptual) chain of IPv6 firewall chains on the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage chain for each chain.

ngIPv6FirewallChainEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical IPv6 firewall chain area on the host.

ngfwIPv6ChainIndex.description: A unique value for each logical IPv6 firewall chain contained by the device.

ngfwIPv6ChainTableIndex.description: Shows what table this chain belongs to. Corresponds to ngfwIPv6TableIndex in ngIPv6FirewallTable.

ngfwIPv6ChainsNumberOfRules.name: ngfwIPv6ChainsNumberOfRules
ngfwIPv6ChainsNumberOfRules.description: The number of rules in this particular chain.

ngIPv6FirewallRuleTable.description: The (conceptual) table of IPv6 firewall rules on the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage rule for each rule.

ngIPv6FirewallRuleEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical IPv6 firewall rule area on the host.

ngfwIPv6RuleIndex.description: A unique value for each logical IPv6 firewall rule contained by the device.

ngfwIPv6RuleTableIndex.name: ngfwIPv6RuleTableIndex
ngfwIPv6RuleTableIndex.description: Shows what table this rule belongs to. Corresponds to ngfwIPv6TableIndex in ngIPv6FirewallTable.

ngfwIPv6RuleSrcIp.description: The rule source IP. Not used and set to all zeroes for IPv4 firewall output.

ngfwIPv6RuleSrcMask.name: ngfwIPv6RuleSrcMask
ngfwIPv6RuleSrcMask.description: The rule source mask in CIDR-compliant format. Not used and set to all zeroes for IPv4 firewall output.

ngfwIPv6RuleDstIp.name: ngfwIPv6RuleDstIp
ngfwIPv6RuleDstIp.description: The rule source IP. Not used and set to all zeroes for IPv4 firewall output.

ngRogueMacStatus.name: ngRogueMacStatus
ngRogueMacStatus.description: Inidicates whether or not Rogue MAC detection has been enabled in Service Manager.

ngRogueMacTable.name: ngRogueMacTable
ngRogueMacTable.description: The (conceptual) table of rogue MACs detected by the device. An entry shall be placed in the storage table for each rogue MAC.

ngRogueMacEntry.name: ngRogueMacEntry
ngRogueMacEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one logical rogue MAC area on the host.

ngrmIndex.name: ngrmIndex
ngrmIndex.description: A unique value for each logical rogue MAC detected by the device.

ngrmMac.name: ngrmMac
ngrmMac.description: The MAC address of this detected rogue MAC. One entry that is zeroed out is returned when there are no rogue MACs detected.

ngrmTimestamp.name: ngrmTimestamp
ngrmTimestamp.description: The date and time of when this rogue MAC was detected. Returned as a regular string in the format MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM:SS. Returns '00/00/0000 00:00:00' when there are no rogue MACs detected. The time returned is the local time on the AT&T VPN Gateway. To determine how the AT&T VPN Gateway's local time relates to UTC view the following OIDs: nghwUtcOffset (current UTC offset), nghwDstAllowed (daylight saving time allowed), nghwDstActive (daylight savings time active). NOTE: This entry is made obsolete by ngrmTimestampDAT.

ngrmIface.name: ngrmIface
ngrmIface.description: The interface this rogue MAC was detected on. One entry that with a value of 'NONE' and a msg is returned when there are no rogue MACs detected.

ngrmTimestampDAT.name: ngrmTimestampDAT
ngrmTimestampDAT.description: The date and time of when this rogue MAC was detected. Returns January 1 year 0 time 0 when there are no rogue MACs detected or the time is unknown. NOTE: This entry replaces ngrmTimestamp.

ngdiPhoneNum.name: ngdiPhoneNum
ngdiPhoneNum.description: The full phone number that will be dialed by the AT&T VPN Gateway. This also includes dial prefix information. For example, the AT&T VPN Gateway might have to dial the number nine and then a comma to access an outside line. The nine and the comma will be included in this entry.

ngdiLastTestResult.name: ngdiLastTestResult
ngdiLastTestResult.description: The result of the last dial test. If no dial test has been performed yet then 'failure' is returned. If a dial test is not needed because dial is currently up then 'success' is returned.

ngdiLastTestCompleteTime.name: ngdiLastTestCompleteTime
ngdiLastTestCompleteTime.description: The approximate time the last dial test completed given in the format MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM:SS. Returns '00/00/0000 00:00:00' when no test is scheduled. or when no test has run yet. If the dial connection is currently in use then the dial test is not needed (since dial is obviously already working). ngdiLastTestCompleteTime is simply updated to the recent time whent the AT&T VPN Gateway last verified that the dial connection was still up. The time returned is the local time on the AT&T VPN Gateway. To determine how the AT&T VPN Gateway's local time relates to UTC view the following OIDs: nghwUtcOffset (current UTC offset), nghwDstAllowed (daylight saving time allowed), nghwDstActive (daylight savings time active). NOTE: This entry is made obsolete by ngdiLastTestCompleteTimeDAT.

ngdiDialTestFailCategory.name: ngdiDialTestFailCategory
ngdiDialTestFailCategory.description: Shows what type of category the dial test failure would be put in. For example, a busy signal would return dialProblemWarning but a bad password would return dialProblemError. If a dial test is not needed because dial is currently up then dialProblemMessage is returned.

ngdiDialTestFailReason.name: ngdiDialTestFailReason
ngdiDialTestFailReason.description: String that shows why the dial test failed. If the test was successful or the dial connection is currently up then 'success' is returned.

ngdiLastTestCompleteTimeDAT.name: ngdiLastTestCompleteTimeDAT
ngdiLastTestCompleteTimeDAT.description: If the dial connection is currently in use then the dial test is not needed (since dial is obviously already working). ngdiLastTestCompleteTimeDAT is simply updated to the recent time whent the AT&T VPN Gateway last verified that the dial connection was still up. Returns January 1 year 0 time 0 when no test is scheduled or when no test has run yet. The time returned is the local time on the AT&T VPN Gateway. To determine how the AT&T VPN Gateway's local time relates to UTC view the following OIDs: nghwUtcOffset (current UTC offset), nghwDstAllowed (daylight saving time allowed), nghwDstActive (daylight savings time active). NOTE: This entry replaces ngdiLastTestCompleteTime.

ngdiSecondaryPhoneNum.name: ngdiSecondaryPhoneNum
ngdiSecondaryPhoneNum.description: Specifies the secondary phone number to be tried for Dial Backup in case the primary Dial Backup phone number is not available.

inbTunLocalIpsecIface.description: The IPsec interface associated with this inbound tunnel.

inbTunType.description: The tunnel type of this inbound tunnel.

inbTunActClientSaNeg.description: Active client SA's negotiated for this inbound tunnel.

inbTunNetIndex.description: A unique value for each logical inbound tunnel's network contained by the device.

inbTunNetTimeEstablished.name: inbTunNetTimeEstablished
inbTunNetTimeEstablished.description: Time this inbound tunnel network was established.

inbTunNetNegIkePhase2Lifet.description: This inbound tunnel network's negotiated IKE Phase 2 lifetime.

inbTunNetEspAlgorithm.name: inbTunNetEspAlgorithm
inbTunNetEspAlgorithm.description: This inbound tunnel network's ESP algorithm.

inbTunNetCompression.description: Is compression negotiated for this inbound tunnel?

inbTunNetClientTransAddr.name: inbTunNetClientTransAddr
inbTunNetClientTransAddr.description: Shows what inbound tunnel this network belongs to. Corresponds to inbTunClientTransAddr in attInbTunEntry.

ngevMac.name: ngevMac
ngevMac.description: The MAC address in Service Manager this device is registered under.

ngevRogueMac.name: ngevRogueMac
ngevRogueMac.description: The MAC address of the unauthorized machine detected when MAC monitoring is enabled.

ngevActiveWanIp.name: ngevActiveWanIp
ngevActiveWanIp.description: The IP address of the active WAN interface. When viewing the output of the SNMP tree this can be determined from the interface statistics. However, for traps the active WAN interface might not be used to send the trap (i.e. it could be down the tunnel. Set to zero if not used.

ngevIpConntrackMaxPercentage.name: ngevIpConntrackMaxPercentage
ngevIpConntrackMaxPercentage.description: An alert will be sent when the ip_conntrack table is within this percentage of the maximum.

ngevIpConntrackCurrentPercentage.name: ngevIpConntrackCurrentPercentage
ngevIpConntrackCurrentPercentage.description: The ip_conntrack table is currently at this percentage of the maximum.

ngevTimeInDial.name: ngevTimeInDial
ngevTimeInDial.description: The number of minutes the device has been connected via dial.

ngevQueryProblem.name: ngevQueryProblem
ngevQueryProblem.description: Used to indicate what type of problem is happening with the device's status. profileNotFound means that a profile for the device was not found on an AT&T Administration Server in any region. discontinuingTheDevice means that the device has gone too long without having a valid profile in any region. bandwNoResults means that a bandwidth test failed and no previous bandwidth test results have been found, which results in the device being marked as discontinued until a bandwidth test works.

ngevTunConnectionId.name: ngevTunConnectionId
ngevTunConnectionId.description: The tunnel connection ID is a unique value assigned to each instance of a tunnel. It is used to associate the tunnel up, tunnel alive, and tunnel down traps together. When a tunnel goes down and is then re-established it will be assigned a new tunnel connection ID.

ngevTunnelDateAndTime.name: ngevTunnelDateAndTime
ngevTunnelDateAndTime.description: The timestamp from when the tunnel came up, tried to come up, or came down.

ngevConnectionType.name: ngevConnectionType
ngevConnectionType.description: Indicates whether the tunnel is via broadband or dial.

ngevAccount.name: ngevAccount
ngevAccount.description: In the tunnel up/down trap it is the customer account used to start the tunnel. In the secondary auth attempt trap it is the account used for the login attempt.

ngevUserid.name: ngevUserid
ngevUserid.description: In the tunnel up/down trap it is the customer userid used to start the tunnel. In the secondary auth attempt trap it is the userid used for the login attempt.

ngevTunConReason.name: ngevTunConReason
ngevTunConReason.description: String that shows a message that explains the results of a tunnel connection attempt.

ngevDialTestFailReason.name: ngevDialTestFailReason
ngevDialTestFailReason.description: String that shows why the dial test failed.

ngevSshSourceIp.name: ngevSshSourceIp
ngevSshSourceIp.description: The IP address of the client that ssh'ed into the device.

ngevRequestorIp.name: ngevRequestorIp
ngevRequestorIp.description: The IP address of the machine that initiated a particular request (reboot, shutdown, secondary auth attempt, etc.). Will be set to loopback if an automated process caused the reboot.

ngevDialTestFailCategory.name: ngevDialTestFailCategory
ngevDialTestFailCategory.description: Shows what type of category the dial test failure would be put in. For example, a busy signal would be a warning but a bad password would be an error.

ngevRogueIp.name: ngevRogueIp
ngevRogueIp.description: The IP address of the unauthorized machine detected when MAC monitoring is enabled. Set to zero if not used.

ngevRogueInterface.name: ngevRogueInterface
ngevRogueInterface.description: The interface of the unauthorized machine detected when MAC monitoring is enabled.

ngevTrapDescription.name: ngevTrapDescription
ngevTrapDescription.description: For MAC monitoring this is the Service Manager description field. Other traps may use this field for other purposes.

ngevLoginResult.name: ngevLoginResult
ngevLoginResult.description: Specifies the result of the secondary login attempt when someone tries to ssh into the AT&T VPN Gateway.

ngevNewLocalID.name: ngevNewLocalID
ngevNewLocalID.description: The userid that the user became after their secondary login attempt was successful. Secondary logins are performed when someone tries to ssh into the AT&T VPN Gateway. The userid that the user became (or tried to become) for their switch user attempt.

ngevOldLocalID.name: ngevOldLocalID
ngevOldLocalID.description: The userid that was in use when the user made their switch user attempt.

ngevMaxTimeInDialUntilAlert.name: ngevMaxTimeInDialUntilAlert
ngevMaxTimeInDialUntilAlert.description: The max number of minutes the device can be connected via dial without a trap being sent for excessive dial. Once this maximum is reached a trap will be sent.

ngevPortDown.name: ngevPortDown
ngevPortDown.description: An individual port that is currently not active. Only used by the AT&T VPN Gateway 8200V.

ngevIPv6ActiveWanIp.name: ngevIPv6ActiveWanIp
ngevIPv6ActiveWanIp.description: The IP address of the active IPv6 WAN interface. When viewing the output of the SNMP tree this can be determined from the interface statistics. However, for traps the active WAN interface might not be used to send the trap (i.e. it could be down the tunnel. Set to zero if not used.

ngevIPv6RogueIp.name: ngevIPv6RogueIp
ngevIPv6RogueIp.description: The IPv6 IP address of the unauthorized machine detected when MAC monitoring is enabled. Set to zero if not used.

ngevIPv6RequestorIp.name: ngevIPv6RequestorIp
ngevIPv6RequestorIp.description: The IPv6 IP address of the machine that initiated a particular request (reboot, shutdown, secondary auth attempt, etc.). Will be set to loopback if an automated process caused the reboot.

ngevCardNotFoundTime.name: ngevCardNotFoundTime
ngevCardNotFoundTime.description: The timestamp that indicates when the AT&T VPN Gateway noted that the required cellular card was missing.

ngevVPNServiceIPv4Address.name: ngevVPNServiceIPv4Address
ngevVPNServiceIPv4Address.description: The VPN Service Address assigned for this tunnel connetion. Will be not set if this is an IPv6 tunnel or the tunnel did not come up.

ngevVPNServiceIPv6Address.name: ngevVPNServiceIPv6Address
ngevVPNServiceIPv6Address.description: The VPN Service Address assigned for this tunnel connetion. Will be not set if this is an IPv4 tunnel or the tunnel did not come up.

ngevTunConReasonNUM.name: ngevTunConReasonNUM
ngevTunConReasonNUM.description: A numeric value that indicates the results of an inbound or outbound tunnel connection attempt.

evIface.name: evIface
evIface.description: The interface in question for this event.

evNotFoundTime.name: evNotFoundTime
evNotFoundTime.description: The timestamp that indicates when the AT&T VPN Gateway noted that the item in question was missing.

evTrapCreatedTime.name: evTrapCreatedTime
evTrapCreatedTime.description: The timestamp that indicates when the trap was actually generated. If informs are in use and the server is temporarily not reachable it could be a long time before the inform is actually received.

evDualWanProb.name: evDualWanProb
evDualWanProb.description: Used to help indicate why IPv4 WAN2 could not be brought up when configured for Dual WAN. The generic 'dwTrapGeneralErr' is used when a specific reason isn't available. 'dwTrapNone' means that there was no error.

evDualWanV6Prob.name: evDualWanV6Prob
evDualWanV6Prob.description: Used to help indicate why IPv6 WAN2 could not be brought up when configured for Dual WAN. The generic 'dwTrapGeneralErr' is used when a specific reason isn't available. 'dwTrapNone' means that there was no error.

evFoundOOB.name: evFoundOOB
evFoundOOB.description: How many OOB cables were detected when at least one was found to be missing.

evExpectedOOB.name: evExpectedOOB
evExpectedOOB.description: How many OOB cables were expected when at least one was found to be missing.

evResult.name: evResult
evResult.description: Generic field to indicate a result.

evResponseMax.name: evResponseMax
evResponseMax.description: Generic field to indicate how long a test waited for a response.

evFailureCount.name: evFailureCount
evFailureCount.description: Generic field to indicate how many failures occurred before this event was generated.

evSendTrapWhen.name: evSendTrapWhen
evSendTrapWhen.description: Generic field used to indicate when to send a trap after a test is performed.

evDataUp10.name: evDataUp10
evDataUp10.description: Average upstream bandwidth measured over a certain time period.

evDataDown10.name: evDataDown10
evDataDown10.description: Average downstream bandwidth measured over a certain time period.

evDataUp11.name: evDataUp11
evDataUp11.description: Average upstream bandwidth measured over a certain time period.

evDataDown11.name: evDataDown11
evDataDown11.description: Average downstream bandwidth measured over a certain time period.

evDataUp12.name: evDataUp12
evDataUp12.description: Average upstream bandwidth measured over a certain time period.

evDataDown12.name: evDataDown12
evDataDown12.description: Average downstream bandwidth measured over a certain time period.

ngevIpConntrackTable.name: ngevIpConntrackTable
ngevIpConntrackTable.description: Sent if the Firewall Connection table reaches the specified threshold.

ngevIpConntrackTableFull.name: ngevIpConntrackTableFull
ngevIpConntrackTableFull.description: Indicates the firewall Connection table has reached capacity.

ngevExcessiveDial.name: ngevExcessiveDial
ngevExcessiveDial.description: The device has been in dial backup longer than the allowed threshold.

ngevActiveWanIpChanged.name: ngevActiveWanIpChanged
ngevActiveWanIpChanged.description: The IP address associated with the active WAN interface has changed. For example, dial backup was initiated because WAN connectivity was lost. Another example is that a PPPoE connection changed its IP address.

ngevRogueMacDetected.name: ngevRogueMacDetected
ngevRogueMacDetected.description: The unauthorized MAC detection feature is enabled and an unauthorized MAC address was detected.

ngevRogueMacNoFile.name: ngevRogueMacNoFile
ngevRogueMacNoFile.description: The unauthorized MAC detection feature is enabled and the authorized MAC file doesn't exist.

ngevNoTeps.name: ngevNoTeps
ngevNoTeps.description: The AT&T VPN Gateway cannot bring up a tunnel to any of the tunnel endpoints.

ngevDeviceDiscoOrNotFound.name: ngevDeviceDiscoOrNotFound
ngevDeviceDiscoOrNotFound.description: Sent if the AT&T VPN Gateway profile is not found. If the AT&T VPN Gateway goes too long without finding its device profile then the device will switch its status to discontinued, which will also trigger a trap/inform.

ngevTunnelUp.name: ngevTunnelUp
ngevTunnelUp.description: Information about the results of a tunnel connection attempt.

ngevTunnelDown.name: ngevTunnelDown
ngevTunnelDown.description: Information about a tunnel disconnect. The one exception is a tunnel 'alive' message, which is sent for a tunnel that is still up. Tunnel 'alive' messages have a ngtuReasonCode of tnlAlive.

ngevDialAutotestFailure.name: ngevDialAutotestFailure
ngevDialAutotestFailure.description: The Dial Autotest (and all specified retries) failed.

ngevDeviceReboot.name: ngevDeviceReboot
ngevDeviceReboot.description: Sent when the device reboots. Requestor IP will be set to loopback if an automated process caused the reboot.

ngevDeviceShutdown.name: ngevDeviceShutdown
ngevDeviceShutdown.description: Sent when the device shuts down.

ngevSshLogin.name: ngevSshLogin
ngevSshLogin.description: Sent when a user accesses the device via SSH.

ngevDhcpPoolExhausted.name: ngevDhcpPoolExhausted
ngevDhcpPoolExhausted.description: Sent when a VLAN's DHCP pool is full.

ngevForTestingOnly.name: ngevForTestingOnly
ngevForTestingOnly.description: Only for use by QA and development for testing.

ngevSecondaryAuthAttempt.name: ngevSecondaryAuthAttempt
ngevSecondaryAuthAttempt.description: Sent when a secondary login attempt occurs. Secondary logins are performed when someone tries to ssh into the AT&T VPN Gateway.

ngevSwitchUseridAttempt.name: ngevSwitchUseridAttempt
ngevSwitchUseridAttempt.description: Sent when a user who is ssh'ed into the AT&T VPN Gateway tries to switch to another userid.

ngev8200VPortDown.name: ngev8200VPortDown
ngev8200VPortDown.description: Sent when either port 7 or 8 is determined to be not active. Only used by the AT&T VPN Gateway 8200V.

ngevCellModemRequired.name: ngevCellModemRequired
ngevCellModemRequired.description: Sent when either the AT&T VPN Gateway boots without a cell modem present or when the AT&T VPN Gateway detects that the cell modem has been removed. The cellular modem must be a supported unit that allows the AT&T VPN Gateway to query its current status.

evVrrpStateChange.name: evVrrpStateChange
evVrrpStateChange.description: Sent when there is a VRRP state change.

evDualWanIfaceProblem.name: evDualWanIfaceProblem
evDualWanIfaceProblem.description: Sent when the AT&T VPN Gateway is configured to also use the second WAN port as Internet Primary and one of the interfaces could not be brought up.

evOOBCableRequired.name: evOOBCableRequired
evOOBCableRequired.description: Optional USB cables allow out of bound (OOB) access to the AT&T VPN Gateway. The number of OOB cables expected to be plugged into the AT&T VPN Gateway is controlled by a setting in Service Manager. This event is sent when either the AT&T VPN Gateway boots without the expected number of cables present, when the AT&T VPN Gateway detects that a cable was present but has been removed, or when all missing cables are returned.

evTunConfigChanged.name: evTunConfigChanged
evTunConfigChanged.description: Sent when the tunnel configuration has changed. All tunnels (if any) are restarted when this occurs.

evDataUsageReport.name: evDataUsageReport
evDataUsageReport.description: Reporting of average bandwidth along with high water mark calculations.

evPingTestResult.name: evPingTestResult
evPingTestResult.description: Sent to indicate the result of a ping test.

evNoIPinCDPool.name: evNoIPinCDPool
evNoIPinCDPool.description: Sent to indicate that there are no available IP addresses in the customer direct pool.

evMaxInbTun.name: evMaxInbTun
evMaxInbTun.description: Sent to indicate that there are no inbound tunnels available.

evReportDualWanIP.name: evReportDualWanIP
evReportDualWanIP.description: Sent to report on the IP addresses in use when both Dual WAN interfaces are up.

ngevBasicComplianceRev.name: ngevBasicComplianceRev
ngevBasicComplianceRev.description: The compliance statement for AT&T VPN Gateway entities which implement this MIB module.

ngEventDataUsageObjectsGroup.name: ngEventDataUsageObjectsGroup
ngEventDataUsageObjectsGroup.description: The event ojects used only for data usage statistics.
